So, i use mech jeb and (in case you do not use it) it shows you the amount of delta-v to expect from each stage of your craft and the total.

Sometimes you need to know what is being delivered by stages 11 through 8. So you need to add these up.

If you use Google as your calculator you can get some strange results.

1317+2018+1100 gives me two tecnical pdfs and two address in the USA.

has anyone else paid attention to these results?

has anyone else struck gold?

i wonder what the NSA think all these numbers i send to the internet mean?

Copying that equation directly into google tells me 4435. It does also give me two PDFs, two addresses, and an education statistics 2018 outlook.

BUT, it gives me an answer.

Exactly, so i'm interested to see if anyone else takes notice of the other results aside from the answer.

Of course i've no idea how many people use the google calculator.
.... nope, I have a calculator in my start menu, much easier.

As a university physics student, I'm drowning in Casio Fx-83/85 calculators as they're the only ones we can use in exams. I think I've got about 4 overall, and a few other calculator models. This means there's pretty much always a real calculator to hand, and I love the clicky feeling of pressing their little buttons
In that case, I have a calculator on my start menu and I own a TI-NSpire CX CAS. That thing is a handheld computer (which can do symbolic algebra and both integral and differential calculus).
